{
  "texts": [
    "Then x ̸ ∈ X, so by refinability for X, there is a y ⊑ x such that for all z ⊑ y, z ̸ ∈ X.",
    "By Definition 5.52.4, since x ∈ S ′ and y ⊑ x, there is a z ∈ S ′ such that z ⊑ y and hence z ⊑ ′ x.",
    "Now for any u ⊑ ′ z, we have u ⊑ y and hence u ̸ ∈ X by the refinability step, so u ̸ ∈ X ′.",
    "Thus, we have shown that if x ̸ ∈ X ′, then there is a z ⊑ ′ x such that for all u ⊑ ′ z, u ̸ ∈ X ′, as desired.For part 2, assuming F is full, so P = RO(S, ⊑), we will show that RO(S ′, ⊑ ′) ⊆ P ′, which with the previous paragraph shows that F ′ is full.",
    "Suppose X ′ ∈ RO(S ′, ⊑ ′)."
  ]
}